Officials say the fire is in an inaccessible part of the mountain range along the Bainskloof Pass, while the fire in Du Toitskloof Pass has been brought under control. CAPE TOWN Firefighters are monitoring a blaze along the Bainskloof Pass outside Wellington. Officials say the fire is in an inaccessible part of the mountain range. Meanwhile, a blaze that raged along the Du Toitskloof Pass has been brought under control. Provincial Disaster Risk Management Head Colin Deiner says, The fire in Du Toitskloof is largely under control. We did need two helicopters to augment the Cape Winelands aerial resources very early this morning. Together with the ground team from the Cape Winelands, and the other emergency services on scene, they worked very well during the day and have been able to contain the fire. 